## M19.1: `pub unsafe sub` and `unsafe pub sub` both compose cleanly.
##
## Per GPT-5.5 entry 37: composition tests are a small but
## worthwhile sanity check. The `(pub child)` and
## `(unsafe_decl child)` IR wrappers each stamp their flag on
## the first newly-added symbol from the wrapped decl, so both
## orderings end up flagging the same Symbol with both flags.
##
## This example exercises both orderings + verifies the
## resulting fn is correctly marked as `is_unsafe = true`
## (callers from safe context fire the M19(4/6) diagnostic).

pub unsafe sub a()
  print(1)

unsafe pub sub b()
  print(2)

sub main()
  unsafe
    a()            # OK: inside unsafe block
    b()            # OK: same
